&#xa0;
[normal]Written evidence from West Midlands scrutiny Network (PEX 0006)[bold]1.0[bold]              [bold]Executive Summary[bold]1.1
[normal]              
[normal]Local Government Scrutiny has an integral role in the accountability framework for many services, including health and social care. The work of the Scrutiny Committees is based on the evidence
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]and since the introduction of local government scrutiny and health scrutiny, Scrutiny Committees have built up a body of knowledge and expertise. The information provided in this memorandum is based
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]on the work of Local Government Scrutiny across 10 West Midlands Local Authorities and will hopefully be of interest and use to the Health Select Committee in its inquiry on Public Expenditure on Health and Social Care.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.0[bold]              [bold]The West Midlands Scrutiny Network[bold]2.1
[normal]              
[normal]The West Midlands Scrutiny Network is an informal network open to all local authorities across the West Midlands. The Network aims to:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]To share experiences and knowledge and to work with other members to develop ideas and good practice which can support and strengthen overview and scrutiny in the region.
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]To provide support and networking opportunities for Councillors and officers who are members of the West Midlands Network
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]To represent the views of West Midlands local authorities' overview and scrutiny members at regional and national events.
[normal]2.2
[normal]              
[normal]To gather information on the work undertaken by Scrutiny Committees across the region relevant to this Inquiry a questionnaire was sent to all Members of the West Midlands Scrutiny Network and the West Midlands Regional Health Scrutiny Forum. A copy of the questionnaire is provided as Appendix 1. This memorandum is not a formal response from Scrutiny in all West Midlands Authorities, rather it provides evidence of work undertaken by Scrutiny in the following authorities that is relevant to the Health Select Committee Inquiry:
